to camp and sat down, a few long thin trees and branches in her arms.  Sitting down, Elektra began to work on the ends of the wood with one of her knives.  The blade wittling down the ends into sharp points.  <br>
<br>
As she worked, Elektra did not look at the others.  But her ears listened keenly.  As she told Hippolyte, she was always listening. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hippolyte>Hippolyte</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 789<br> <font color=#993300>(2/23/03 12:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=62>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/Hippwknife1ezboard.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Watching.</span><hr size=1> Cassandra and Kara had begun working on making the camp comfortable for any of their female friends who may decide to leave the Romans.  They were thankful for the Amazons help.  But, were not sure exactly what the plans were.<br>
<br>
Kara walked over to Hippolyte who was now brushing down her mare.  The young woman was totally fascinated by the amazons. They were like heros.  Not the animals that they had heard about in the old stories.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Hippolyte, I want to ride with you tonight.  I want to help rescue my friends.&quot;  Kara pleaded.<br>
<br>
Hipp looked over to the young girl.  And a soft smile lifted on her lips.  &quot;Kara...you are not trained as a warrior.  It would be safer for you and Cassandra if you both stay behind.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;But, I can fight...I know I can.&quot;  pleaded Kara again.  &quot;I want to be an amazon.&quot;<br>
<br>
Hippolyte sighed and glanced over at Cassandra, who was watching.  Cassandra walked up to the both of them.<br>
<br>
&quot;Queen Hippolyte,&quot; Cassandra began.  &quot;Once you help save some of our friends.  What are we to do?  I mean, some may want to go back to find their families.  But, there are not many of us with any families left, thanks to the Romans.  I know we are not amazons or warriors.  But, we can learn.  I am a good cook besides.&quot;  She smiled at the amazon..hopinig Hipp would hear them out.<br>
<br>
&quot;Cassandra, if you would like to come live with the amazons and learn our way.  I would be proud.  But, tonight...I cannot take Kara.  If she wants to be a warrior.  She has to know.. it comes with training.. not a dream.&quot;<br>
<br>
Kara sighed and looked to Cassandra.<br>
<br>
&quot;I tell you what,&quot; said Hippolyte.  &quot;You remain here at camp and keep it safe...along with your sister.  In that...you are a warrior.&quot;<br>
<br>
Kara's smile grew larger and she glanced at Cassandra then back to Hippolyte. &quot;It will be done, Queen Hippolyte.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Efharisto,&quot; thanked Hipp.<br>
<br>
Kara and Cassandra then walked back to their huts.  There was so much to do.  And they could not wait to see their friends again. <p>@xxx}}::::::::::::::::::::>

"We ride tonight!  With the strength that Hera has given
us-- and the strength that we have _earned_ for ourselves!  Take
what you need, but be quick.  Stay only until the sound of horn.
The moment you hear it-- we ride away.  Now-- to your horses."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dawnithinia>Dawnithinia </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 441<br> <font color=#993300>(2/23/03 3:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=63>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The men.</span><hr size=1>  As the roman men began to leave the forest, Dawn continued in the trees following them. Unlike Marpe, Dawn was to follow, Dawn was to learn all that she could, and she would.<br>
<br>
 She stayed close to the ground, grabbing branches that would bring her almost to view, but in silence the men would never know. Emerald eyes never left the men, they continue to rapidly search them for their weaponry, and anything else that would help them in their battle.<br>
<br>
 The men stopped, as did Dawn. Just between their village and the rest of the forest, and met with more men. Dawn almost instinctively growled, but held back. Settling into her tree, she began to watch once more. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daughterofshylock>Daughter of Shylock</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.picturesof.net/_wallpaper/rose_Dsc08151_WP.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 203<br> <font color=#993300>(2/23/03 5:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=64>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.picturesof.net/_wallpaper/rose_Dsc08151_WP.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The men.</span><hr size=1> Alysia nodded to Hippolyte and began to ready the weapons. Likewise she set up a small healing station at a nearby tree. Alysia wasn't stupid, there were some mortals here. She herself had died before and people could get hurt.<br>
<br>
Once everything was settled she whistled for her wolves who came right to her side.<br>
<br>
&quot;Aeceus, Scythe . . . follow the others and then split. Watch the Roman village, let out a howl if you see anything that should bring me there.&quot;<br>
<br>
Each nodded and fled into the woods. Alysia watched as her fellow sisters left.<br>
<br>
&quot;Safe passage sisters.&quot; <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">~*~ Jessica ~*~<br>
