Setting them aside, Elektra walked over to the hole that Hippolyte had begun to work on.  Digging the whole deep enough and yet slim in width for an amazon to hide in.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daughterofshylock>Daughter of Shylock</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.picturesof.net/_wallpaper/rose_Dsc08151_WP.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 214<br> <font color=#993300>(2/26/03 11:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=69>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.picturesof.net/_wallpaper/rose_Dsc08151_WP.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The men.</span><hr size=1> The two wolves went into the woods. Aeceus perched himself near a high area overlooking the village. Scythe, being close to Themiscryans always, took to Hippolyte's side.<br>
<br>
Hippolyte knew how protective Alysia was over her athelfi. And the fact that she was back at camp preparing more weapons, made her uneasy. Scythe looked up at Hippolyte and then turned his bright blue eyes into the darkness of the trees. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">~*~ Jessica ~*~<br>
